{{Infobox person | name = Ernst Tanner | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1946|7|24}} | birth_place = [[Bargen, Schaffhausen|Bargen SH]], [[Switzerland]] | occupation = Chairman of the Board of [[Lindt & Sprüngli]] }}
'''Ernst Tanner''' (born 24 July 1946, resident in [[Bargen, Schaffhausen]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.munzinger.de/search/portrait/Ernst+Tanner/0/22587.html |title=Ernst Tanner |publisher=Munzinger |access-date=4 January 2018}}</ref>) is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] manager and entrepreneur. He is Chairman of the Board of the chocolate manufacturer [[Lindt & Sprüngli]].
== Life == After earning his undergraduate degree in business administration, Tanner continued his education at [[business school]]s in [[London]] and [[Harvard Business School|Harvard]]. He worked for over 25 years in a leading management position in the [[Johnson & Johnson]] Group in [[Europe]] and the [[United States|USA]]. From 1993 to 2016 he was Managing Director ([[Chief executive officer|CEO]]) of Lindt & Sprüngli, since 1994 he has been Chairman of the Board of Directors, for many years as a double mandate as CEO. He has been a member of the Board of Directors since 1995, Vice President of the Board of Directors since 2011 where he was a member since 2002 and, since 2014, Chairman of the Compensation Committee of the [[Swatch Group]]. He is also a member of the advisory board of the German [[Krombacher Brauerei]] and the Austrian [[Signa Holding]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://report.lindt-spruengli.com/16/ar/de/02-03-verwaltungsrat/ |title=Verwaltungsrat |publisher=Lindt & Sprüngli |access-date=4 January 2018}}</ref>
