{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Gerrit Thomas Ferreira | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1948|04|06}} | birth_place = | residence = [[Johannesburg]], South Africa | alma mater = [[University of Stellenbosch]] | networth = [[United States dollar|$]] 510 million <ref>https://www.forbes.com/profile/gerrit-thomas-gt-ferreira/</ref> | nationality = [[South African]] | Source of income = Banking & Insurance | occupation = Businessman | known_for = | children = 2 }} '''Gerrit Thomas Ferreira''' also known as GT Ferreira is a South African businessman and banker who is the Chairman of [[Rand Merchant Insurance Holdings|RMI Holdings]]. He is also one of the co-founder of [[FirstRand Bank|Firstrand]] bank in South Africa.
==Biography==
Gerrit Ferreira got his MBA degree from [[University of Stellenbosch]]. In 1977, he co-founded FirstRand's predecessor, Rand Consolidated Investing along with Paul Harris and [[Lauritz Dippenaar]]. Previously, he served as MD of [[RMB Holdings]] between 1985-88.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://saentrepreneurs.co.za/gerrit-gt-ferreira-rmb-holdings-first-rand-limited/|title=Gerrit GT Ferreira - RMB Holdings (First Rand) - SA Entrepreneurs Mag|website=saentrepreneurs.co.za|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-12}}</ref>
