{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox person | name = Pete Cashmore | image = Pete Cashmore 2012 Shankbone.JPG | image_size = | caption = Cashmore at the [[2012 Time 100]] gala | pseudonym = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1985|9|18}}<ref name="mediabistro">{{cite web|url=http://www.mediabistro.com/articles/details.asp?aID=10600& |title=SO WHAT DO YOU DO, PETE CASHMORE, MASHABLE FOUNDER AND CEO? |publisher=Mediabistro |date=19 August 2009 |first=Joe |last=Ciarallo |accessdate=2 December 2014 }}</ref> | birth_place = [[Banchory]], Scotland | spouse = | signature = | website = {{url|http://mashable.com/|Mashable.com}} }} '''Pete Cashmore''' (born 18 September 1985) is the CEO and founder of the popular blog [[Mashable]],<ref name="Pete Cashmore">{{cite web|title=Pete Cashmore|url=http://mashable.com/people/petecashmore/|website=Mashable|publisher=Mashable|accessdate=27 October 2014}}</ref> a [[Technorati]] Top 10 blog worldwide.<ref>{{citation | url=http://technorati.com/blogs/top100/ | title=Technorati Top 100 (1–25) | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120826062604/http://technorati.com/blogs/top100 | archivedate=26 August 2012 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> He grew up in [[Banchory]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/small-business/sb-managing/leadership/14-things-you-didnt-know-about-mashables-pete-cashmore/article4260668/ |title=14 Things You Didn't Know About Mashable's Pete Cashmore |work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |date=26 May 2011 |location=Toronto |deadurl=yes |first=Teri |last=Evans |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130617033432/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/small-business/sb-managing/leadership/14-things-you-didnt-know-about-mashables-pete-cashmore/article4260668/ |archivedate=17 June 2013 }}</ref> and founded Mashable in [[Aberdeenshire, Scotland]] in 2005 when he was 19.<ref name="Pete Cashmore"/>
In 2009, Cashmore was recognized in ''[[Inc. (magazine)|Inc.]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s "30 Under 30", ''[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki> "Top 25 Web Celebs",<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/2009/01/29/web-celebrities-internet-technology-webceleb09_0129_top_slide_7.html | work=Forbes | first=David M. | last=Ewalt | title=The Web Celeb 25}}</ref> and ''[[The Huffington Post]]'''s "Top 10 Game Changers 2009".<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/11/06/huffpost-game-changers-wh_n_347226.html | work=Huffington Post | first=Alex | last=Leo | title=HuffPost Game Changers: Who Is The Ultimate Game Changer In Technology? | date=6 November 2009}}</ref> Cashmore was also named the most influential Briton and most influential Twitter user in the world in 2009 by [[INQ]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inqmobile.com/lang/en/blog/twitterati/|title=INQ’s Twitterati List Revealed|accessdate=21 December 2009}}</ref>
Cashmore previously wrote a weekly column on technology and social media for [[CNN]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/TECH/05/21/cashmore.iphone.cool/index.html?iref=allsearch | work=CNN | title=Has the iPhone lost its cool? | date=21 May 2010}}</ref> In 2012, Cashmore made [[Time (magazine)|Time magazine]]'s list of the 100 most influential people.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2111975_2111976_2112136,00.html |title=Pete Cashmore - Time 100 2012 |last=Milano |first=Alyssa |authorlink=Alyssa Milano |date=18 April 2012}}</ref>
In 2017, Mashable was sold to [[Ziff Davis]] for 50 million dollars, and over 50 staff members were laid off.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/12/05/mashable-laying-off-50-people-as-it-refocuses-toward-tech-news-after-fire-sale-to-ziff-davis/|title=Mashable laying off 50 people as it refocuses toward tech news after fire sale to Ziff Davis|work=TechCrunch|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref>
In November of 2018, after his social media profiles were edited to include "Now: Taking some time off and working on something new," it was announced that Cashmore would be leaving [[Mashable]] at the end of the year. The general manager of Ziff Davis Tech (Mashable's parent company), Mike Finnerty, confirmed this.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedrum.com/news/2018/11/16/pete-cashmore-leave-mashable-end-year|title=Pete Cashmore to leave Mashable at end of year|work=The Drum|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://marketingindustrynews.com/2018/11/16/pete-cashmore-to-leave-mashable-at-end-of-year/|title=Pete Cashmore to leave Mashable at end of year - Marketing Industry News|website=marketingindustrynews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref>
