{{Infobox journal | title = Transportation Science | cover = | editor = | discipline = [[Transport]] | formernames = | abbreviation = Transp. Sci. | publisher = [[Institute for Operations Research and the Management Sciences]] | country = United States | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1967–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 3.295 | impact-year = 2015 | website = http://www.informs.org/Journal/TranSci | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0041-1655 | eISSN = 1526-5447 }} '''''Transportation Science''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by the [[Institute for Operations Research and the Management Sciences]] (INFORMS). The studies published in the journal apply [[operations research]] techniques to problems in the full range of [[transport]]ation sectors, including [[air travel]], [[rail transport]], commuter lines, and vehicular travel/traffic. From time to time, studies published in ''Transportation Science'' are featured in mainstream publications.<ref>[https://www.usnews.com/usnews/culture/articles/980427/archive_003815.htm US News, 1998]</ref>
