{{Infobox football biography |embed = | name = Wan Chi Keung | fullname = Wan Chi Keung | birth_date = {{birth date|df=y|1956|05|01}} | birth_place = [[Hong Kong]] | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2010|02|16|1956|05|01}} | death_place = [[Hong Kong]] | position = [[Striker (football)|Centre forward]] | years1 = 1974–1983 | years2 = 1983–1984 | years3 = 1984–1985 | years4 = 1985–1986 | years5 = 1986–1988 | years6 = 1988–1989 | clubs1 = [[South China AA|South China]] | clubs2 = [[Seiko (football)|Seiko]] | clubs3 = HK Electric | clubs4 = [[Seiko (football)|Seiko]] | clubs5 = [[South China AA|South China]] | clubs6 = [[Double Flower FA|Double Flower]] | goals4 = 1 | goals5 = 11 | goals6 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 1974–1975 | nationalteam1 = [[Hong Kong Olympic football team|Hong Kong U19]] | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | nationalyears2 = 1976–1986 | nationalteam2 = [[Hong Kong national football team|Hong Kong]] | nationalcaps2 = | nationalgoals2 = 32 (18) | module = }} {{Chinese name|[[Yǐn (surname)|Wan]]}} '''Wan Chi Keung''' ({{zh|t=尹志強|s=尹志强|j=wan<sup>5</sup> zi<sup>3</sup> koeng<sup>4</sup>}}; May 1, 1956 – February 16, 2010) was an [[Association football]] player, actor and businessman from [[Hong Kong]].
Known as "Asia's top striker"<ref name="HK football star Wan Chi-keung dies">{{cite news|title=HK football star Wan Chi-keung dies| date=2010-02-16|url=http://www.rthk.org.hk/rthk/news/englishnews/20100216/news_20100216_56_647744.htm|accessdate=2010-02-16}}</ref> Wan was a key player for the [[Hong Kong national football team]] in the 1970s and 1980s. He played for [[South China AA]] and [[Seiko (football)]] in the [[Hong Kong First Division League]].<ref>http://881903.com/Page/ZH-TW/newsdetail.aspx?ItemId=202350</ref> After retirement, he became an actor. His most famous role was a senior police officer in the [[Infernal Affairs]] trilogy.<ref name="Actress Michelle Yim's Boyfriend Dies"/>
He had been dating veteran actress [[Michelle Yim]] for almost 30 years.<ref name="Actress Michelle Yim's Boyfriend Dies">{{cite news|title=Actress Michelle Yim's Boyfriend Dies|date=2010-02-17|url=http://english.cri.cn/6666/2010/02/17/1261s550690.htm|accessdate=2010-02-16}}</ref>
He was diagnosed with [[nasopharyngeal carcinoma]] in the early 1990s but the condition improved over the years. On 16 February 2010, Wan died in [[Hong Kong]].<ref name="HK football star Wan Chi-keung dies"/><ref name="Actress Michelle Yim's Boyfriend Dies"/>
